From: Danilo Diaz <danilodt@gmail.com>
Date: Wed, 14 May 2026 23:00:01 -0500
Subject: [PATCH 2/3] meta-balena-raspberrypi: local.conf.sample: list
 revpi-core-se

Add revpi-core-se to the commented-out MACHINE list in the sample
local.conf so developers can uncomment it for a manual bitbake build.

Reproduces the equivalent change from closed upstream PR #1285,
rebased onto balena-os/balena-raspberrypi @ v6.12.3+rev4.
---
 layers/meta-balena-raspberrypi/conf/samples/local.conf.sample | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/layers/meta-balena-raspberrypi/conf/samples/local.conf.sample b/layers/meta-balena-raspberrypi/conf/samples/local.conf.sample
--- a/layers/meta-balena-raspberrypi/conf/samples/local.conf.sample
+++ b/layers/meta-balena-raspberrypi/conf/samples/local.conf.sample
@@ -5,6 +5,7 @@
 #MACHINE ?= "raspberrypi3-64"
 #MACHINE ?= "revpi-connect-s"
 #MACHINE ?= "revpi-connect-4"
+#MACHINE ?= "revpi-core-se"
 #MACHINE ?= "raspberrypi4-64"
 #MACHINE ?= "raspberrypi400-64"
 #MACHINE ?= "raspberrypicm4-ioboard"
--
